Package: valiCATE
Type: Package
Title: Validation of CATE Predictions via CWATE and NCWATE
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Riccardo", "Di Francesco", email = "rdif@sam.sdu.dk", role = c("cre", "aut")),
    person("Michael", "Knaus", email = "michael.knaus@uni-tuebingen.de", role = c("ctb")))
Maintainer: Riccardo Di Francesco <rdif@sam.sdu.dk>
Description: Validates machine learning predictions of conditional average treatment effects (CATEs)
    using the Centered-Weighted Average Treatment Effect (CWATE) and its normalized counterpart
    (NCWATE). These estimands unify existing validation tools (BLP, AUTOC, QINI, AUC-HVL) as special
    cases of a single framework. AIPW-based estimation with cross-fitted nuisance functions provides
    valid inference under weak conditions.
